# Usage:
# 1. Ensure you have the "REST Client" extension installed in VS Code.
# 2. This file expects variables to be defined in your environment or Settings.json.
#    However, for quick testing, you can uncomment the @ lines below and paste your keys,
#    OR just rely on the extension reading your .env file if configured.

@baseUrl = https://paper-api.alpaca.markets
@apiKey = {{$dotenv ALPACA_API_KEY}}
@secretKey = {{$dotenv ALPACA_SECRET_KEY}}
@symbol = {{$dotenv TRADING_SYMBOL}}

### 1. Get Account Details
# Verifies connectivity and authentication
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/account
APCA-API-KEY-ID: {{apiKey}}
APCA-API-SECRET-KEY: {{secretKey}}

### 2. Get Market Clock
# Checks if the market is open
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/clock
APCA-API-KEY-ID: {{apiKey}}
APCA-API-SECRET-KEY: {{secretKey}}

### 3. Get All Positions
# See what you are currently holding
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/positions
APCA-API-KEY-ID: {{apiKey}}
APCA-API-SECRET-KEY: {{secretKey}}

### 4. Get Latest Quote for Symbol
# Checks data permissions
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/stocks/{{symbol}}/quotes/latest
APCA-API-KEY-ID: {{apiKey}}
APCA-API-SECRET-KEY: {{secretKey}}

### 5. Get Latest Bar for Symbol
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/stocks/{{symbol}}/bars/latest
APCA-API-KEY-ID: {{apiKey}}
APCA-API-SECRET-KEY: {{secretKey}}

### 6. Place a Limit Buy Order (Paper Trading Only!)
# Be careful running this!
# POST {{baseUrl}}/v2/orders
# APCA-API-KEY-ID: {{apiKey}}
# APCA-API-SECRET-KEY: {{secretKey}}
# Content-Type: application/json

# {
#     "symbol": "{{symbol}}",
#     "qty": 1,
